text: The Clandestine Immigration and Naval Museum (also called The National Israeli Museum of the Sea) is a museum in Haifa. It covers the history of Israel at sea, starting with clandestine immigration during the British Mandate of Palestine. It also includes the history of the Israeli navy. == Other websites == * The Clandestine Immigration and Naval Museum on IMuseum Category:Museums in Haifa
